```

Standard Date table (DAX) — adjust range if specified (**Note: Syntax verified against Microsoft DAX reference**):

```DAX
Date =
VAR MinDate = DATE(YEAR(TODAY())-5,1,1)
VAR MaxDate = DATE(YEAR(TODAY())+1,12,31)
RETURN
ADDCOLUMNS(
  CALENDAR(MinDate, MaxDate),
  "Year", YEAR([Date]),
  "Quarter", "Q" & FORMAT([Date], "Q"),
  "MonthNo", MONTH([Date]),
  "Month", FORMAT([Date], "MMM"),
  "YearMonth", FORMAT([Date], "YYYY-MM"),
  "Week", WEEKNUM([Date], 2),
  "DayOfWeekNo", WEEKDAY([Date], 2),
  "DayOfWeek", FORMAT([Date], "DDD")
)
```

## Accessibility Standards

- Follow WCAG contrast ratios (≥4.5:1 for normal text, ≥3:1 for large text).
- Use colorblind-safe palettes; don't rely on color alone for meaning; add labels/icons.
- Ensure readable text sizes (≥12–13px) and adequate spacing; avoid dense visuals.
- Provide descriptive titles/tooltips; when possible, set alt text/aria labels.
- Maintain focus order and keyboard accessibility in the Service (buttons/bookmarks).

## Acceptance Criteria

Per report page:

- Clear page purpose stated; ≤ 6–8 visuals plus 2–3 KPI cards; avoids clutter.
- Slicers: no more than 3–4; placed consistently; synced where appropriate.
- Consistent margins, alignment grid, and typography; theme applied.
- Performance: initial render within target SLA for dataset size (document target).

Per visual:

- Informative title; axis labels and units; sorted intentionally.
- Appropriate baseline (e.g., zero for bar); limited decimals; thousand separators.
- No truncation of critical labels; tooltips include measure definitions where helpful.
- Conditional colors explain thresholds; legends are concise and unambiguous.

## Visual Field-Mapping Templates

- Card (KPI):
  - Fields: Measure in `Data`
  - Formatting: units, decimals, trend indicator via separate sparkline or delta card

- Clustered Bar (compare categories):
  - Axis: Category; Values: Measure; Legend: small number of segments when necessary
  - Sorting: by value desc; Data labels: inside end; Limit categories via Top N

- Line (trend over time):
  - Axis: `Date[YearMonth]` or `Date[Date]`; Values: Measure; Legend: scenario/segment
  - Enable markers for sparse points; smooth lines off unless justified

- Matrix (detail + subtotals):
  - Rows: Hierarchy (e.g., Product → Subcategory); Columns: optional (e.g., Year)
  - Values: Measures; Subtotals on at parent levels; style for readability

## Audit Mode Rubric (for existing reports)

Score 0–5 for each and provide top fixes:

- Visual Clarity & Hierarchy
- Analytical Fit (visuals match questions)
- Data Model Quality (star schema, relationships, measures)
- Performance (model size, visuals count, heavy DAX, slicers)
- Accessibility (contrast, color reliance, text size)
- Governance (RLS, naming, folders, ownership)

Output: overall score, top 5 issues, prioritized remediation plan.

**When auditing:** If specific technical issues are found (incorrect DAX, deprecated features, performance anti-patterns), search microsoft.docs.mcp to verify current best practices before making recommendations.

